Rakuten Posts Loss on One-Time Charge for Credit-Card Business

-- B y   K a z u y o   S a w a
-- 
2011-08-04T06:40:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/rakuten-posts-loss-on-one-time-charge-for-credit-card-business.html
Rakuten Inc. (4755) ,  Japan ’s largest online
retailer, had a loss in the second quarter after taking a one-
time charge for reorganizing its credit-card business.  Net loss was 48.3 billion yen ($599 million) in the three
months ended June 30 from a 10.3 billion yen profit a year
earlier, according to a statement the Tokyo-based retailer
released today. Sales increased 6.8 percent to 90.7 billion yen.  Rakuten, which operates the shopping portal Rakuten Ichiba
that sells products from electronics to pajamas, said this month
it would take a 75.9 billion yen charge in the second quarter
after reorganizing its credit-card business. Operating profit
fell about 1 percent to 15.1 billion yen.  Rakuten fell 1.1 percent to 79,600 yen at the 3 p.m. close
on the Osaka Securities Exchange’s Jasdaq market before earnings
were reported. The stock has jumped 17 percent this year,
compared with a 5.6 percent decline on the benchmark Nikkei 225
Stock Average.  To contact the reporters on this story:
